  "local_port": 58866,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should be my daily schedule?",
  "response": "Creating a daily schedule depends on your personal goals, responsibilities, and preferences. Below is a general template you can customize to fit your needs:\n\n### Morning Routine\n1. **Wake Up** (e.g., 6:00 AM)\n   - Stretch or do light exercises\n   - Hydrate (drink water)\n   - Personal hygiene\n\n2. **Breakfast** (e.g., 6:30 AM)\n   - Eat a healthy meal\n   - Plan your day\n\n3. **Personal Development** (e.g., 7:00 AM)\n   - Read or listen to a podcast\n   - Meditate or journal\n\n### Work/Study\n4. **Work/Study Session 1** (e.g., 8:00 AM)\n   - Focus on high-priority tasks\n   - Take short breaks (e.g., 5-10 minutes)\n\n5. **Mid-Morning Break** (e.g., 10:00 AM)\n   - Stretch or take a quick walk\n   - Hydrate\n\n6. **Work/Study Session 2** (e.g., 10:15 AM)\n   - Continue working on important tasks\n\n### Midday Routine\n7. **Lunch Break** (e.g., 12:00 PM)\n   - Eat a balanced meal\n   - Relax or engage in a hobby\n\n### Afternoon Routine\n8. **Work/Study Session 3** (e.g., 1:00 PM)\n   - Focus on secondary tasks\n   - Take short breaks\n\n9. **Mid-Afternoon Break** (e.g., 3:00 PM)\n   - Hydrate and stretch\n\n10. **Work/Study Session 4** (e.g., 3:15 PM)\n    - Wrap up tasks and plan for the next day\n\n### Evening Routine\n11. **Exercise** (e.g., 5:00 PM)\n    - Engage in physical activity (e.g., gym, yoga, running)\n\n12. **Dinner** (e.g., 6:00 PM)\n    - Eat a nutritious meal\n    - Spend time with family or friends\n\n13. **Relaxation** (e.g., 7:00 PM)\n    - Watch a movie, read a book, or engage in a hobby\n\n14. **Preparation for Tomorrow** (e.g., 8:00 PM)\n    - Review your schedule\n    - Prepare clothes and items needed for the next day\n\n15. **Personal Reflection/Gratitude** (e.g., 9:00 PM)\n    - Journal about your day\n    - Practice gratitude\n\n### Night Routine\n16. **Wind Down** (e.g., 9:30 PM)\n    - Limit screen time\n    - Engage in a calming activity (e.g., gentle stretching, meditation)\n\n17. **Sleep** (e.g., 10:00 PM)\n    - Aim for 7-8 hours of sleep\n\n### Tips for Customization:\n- **Adjust the timing** based on your wake-up and sleep schedule.\n- **Include breaks** to avoid burnout.\n- **Prioritize tasks** according to your goals and deadlines.\n- **Incorporate flexibility** for unexpected events or changes.\n\nFeel free to tweak this template to better fit your unique needs and preferences!",
